message: "If you use quarto-livefigures in your work, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "quarto-livefigures: editable, version-controlled figures for Quarto"
authors:
  - family-names: Davis
    given-names: Sean
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-8991-6458"
    email: seandavi@gmail.com
repository-code: "https://github.com/seandavi/quarto-livefigures"
url: "https://livefigures.seandavis.net"
license: MIT
version: 0.8.0
date-released: 2026-07-21
keywords:
  - quarto
  - figures
  - diagrams
  - reproducible-research
  - excalidraw
  - vega-lite
  - graphviz
  - ai-agents
abstract: >-
  A Quarto extension that renders editable, version-controlled figure
  sources (Excalidraw, Vega-Lite, Graphviz, PlantUML, and fourteen other
  plain-text formats) at build time, with content-addressed caching and
  native Quarto figure semantics. Formats are selected for LLM fluency so
  that AI agents can create, revise, and review figures as ordinary
  source-code changes.
